TITLE: Implementing WebAssembly Module Instantiation in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use js-sys to compile, instantiate, and run a WebAssembly module from within Rust code compiled to WebAssembly. It includes functions for creating a module, instantiating it, and executing its exported functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen/blob/main/guide/src/examples/wasm-in-wasm.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use js_sys::*;
use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;

#[wasm_bindgen]
pub fn run() -> Result<JsValue, JsValue> {
    // Create our `WebAssembly.Module`
    let module = include_bytes!("add.wasm");
    let module = WebAssembly::Module::new(&Uint8Array::from(module.as_ref()))?;

    // Create the import object for the module
    let import_object = Object::new();

    // Instantiate the module
    let instance = WebAssembly::Instance::new(&module, &import_object)?;

    // Extract the `add` function from the module
    let add = Reflect::get(&instance.exports(), &"add".into())?;
    let add = add.dyn_ref::<Function>().unwrap();

    // Invoke the `add` function
    let result = add.call2(&JsValue::undefined(), &1.into(), &2.into())?;

    // Return the result
    Ok(result)
}

```

