TITLE: Importing JavaScript Functions in Rust with wasm-bindgen
DESCRIPTION: Rust code using wasm-bindgen to import JavaScript functions and classes. Shows how to declare external JavaScript functions and use them in Rust with proper type bindings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen/blob/main/guide/src/examples/import-js.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;

#[wasm_bindgen(module = "/defined-in-js.js")]
extern "C" {
    fn foo(a: i32) -> i32;

    type Bar;

    #[wasm_bindgen(constructor)]
    fn new() -> Bar;

    #[wasm_bindgen(method)]
    fn add(this: &Bar, a: i32) -> i32;

    type Content;

    #[wasm_bindgen(constructor)]
    fn new() -> Content;

    #[wasm_bindgen(method, getter)]
    fn name(this: &Content) -> String;

    fn get_content() -> Content;
}

#[wasm_bindgen]
pub fn test() {
    let x = foo(1);
    console_log!("{}", x);

    let bar = Bar::new();
    let y = bar.add(2);
    console_log!("{}", y);

    let content = get_content();
    console_log!("{}", content.name());
}
```

