TITLE: Implementing Rust Character Counter for WebAssembly
DESCRIPTION: Rust implementation of a Counter struct that works with character types through wasm-bindgen. Demonstrates conversion of Rust char to JavaScript string for WebAssembly interop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen/blob/main/guide/src/examples/char.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;

#[wasm_bindgen]
struct Counter {
    key: char,
    count: i32,
}

#[wasm_bindgen]
impl Counter {
    #[wasm_bindgen(constructor)]
    pub fn new(key: char) -> Counter {
        Counter {
            key,
            count: 0,
        }
    }

    pub fn key(&self) -> char {
        self.key
    }

    pub fn count(&self) -> i32 {
        self.count
    }

    pub fn increment(&mut self) {
        self.count += 1;
    }
}
```

