TITLE: Implementing Variadic Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a variadic function in JavaScript that sums an arbitrary number of arguments. It shows both the old way using the 'arguments' object and the new way using rest parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen/blob/main/guide/src/reference/attributes/on-js-imports/variadic.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function sum(...rest) {
    let i;
    // the old way
    let old_way = 0;
    for (i=0; i<arguments.length; i++) {
        old_way += arguments[i];
    }
    // the new way
    let new_way = 0;
    for (i=0; i<rest.length; i++) {
        new_way += rest[i];
    }
    // both give the same answer
    assert(old_way === new_way);
    return new_way;
}
```

