TITLE: Accessing Skipped Fields in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the behavior of accessing struct fields in JavaScript where skipped fields are undefined. Shows that while you can shadow a skipped field with a new value, it won't affect the actual value in Rust memory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen/blob/main/guide/src/reference/attributes/on-rust-exports/skip.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import('./pkg/').then(rust => {
    let foo = rust.Foo.new();

    // bar is accessible by getter
    console.log(foo.bar);
    // field marked with `skip` is undefined
    console.log(foo.baz);      

    // you can shadow it
    foo.baz = 45;       
    // so accessing by getter will return `45`
    // but it won't affect real value in rust memory
    console.log(foo.baz);
});
```

